definition.value: Soil which has elevated concentrations of metals.

This could be demoted to an inferred class if issues with double inheritance arise.

value.value: A tannery is a building in which the skins of animals are treated with chemicals to alter the structure of their constituent proteins, creating leather.

definition.value: Manure which is primarily composed of pig feces.

value.value: An industrial building is a building within which goods are produced and, optionally, stored or within which services are rendered.

definition.value: It's possible that this will become an inferred class in the future. The United Nations' International Standard Industrial Classification should be referred to when expanding this branch. ISIC can also be used to identify processes. See http://unstats.un.org/unsd/cr/registry/regcst.asp?Cl=27&Lg=1.

value.value: A dairy is a building in which animal milk is harvested and, optionally, processed for human consumption.

definition.value: 'Terminology differs between countries. For example, in the United States, the entire dairy farm is commonly called a "dairy." The building or farm area where milk is harvested from the cow is often called a "milking parlor" or "parlor." The farm area where milk is stored in bulk tanks is known as the farm's "milk house." Milk is then hauled (usually by truck) to a "dairy plant," also referred to as a "dairy", where raw milk is further processed and prepared for commercial sale of dairy products. In New Zealand, farm areas for milk harvesting are also called "milking parlours", and are historically known as "milking sheds."' https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dairy

A food processing building is a building in which materials that contain or consist of essential body nutrients - such as carbohydrates, fats, proteins, vitamins, or minerals - and may be ingested and assimilated by an organism to produce energy, stimulate growth, and maintain life are converted alternative forms.
The semantics of food are being handled by FOODON http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/foodon.owl

value.value: A bakery is a building in which raw flour-based food is baked in an oven to produce food products such as bread, cakes, pastries, and pies. These products are often sold from the bakery itself.

definition.value: A bakery is a food processing building and a 'food shop' at the same time. This needs to be resolved.

value.value: An agricultural byproduct, the dry stalk of a cereal plant, after the nutrient grain or seed has been removed.

A brewery is a building in which alcoholic beverages are produced by brewing, that is, steeping a starch source (commonly cereal grains) in water and fermenting the resulting sweet liquid with yeast. At times, the products are also sold from the brewery.
A manufactured product which has been formulated to modifying the appearance of external human anatomical parts.

A cosmetic product which has been formulated 2) to have a viscous, fatty, liquid consistency resembling the fat-rich component of milk and 2) to be applied to human facial skin to modify its appearance or functioning.

definition.value: A product which is composed primarily of paper.
A paper product which is used as legal tender in economic or other monetary trasactions.

value.value: A sake brewery is a brewery which produces rice wine by fermenting rice which has been polished to remove the bran.

definition.value: Soil which has increased levels of chalk.

value.value: A building or collection of co-located buildings constructed for the purpose of undertaking scientific research.
A layer of impurities that accumulates at the surface of a liquid (especially water or molten metal).
A warehouse is a building which is used for the storage of goods.
A tobacco warehouse is a warehouse used to store cured leaves of plants from the genus Nicotiana, primarily  N. tabacum and N. rustica.

definition.value: A creamery is a part of a dairy where cream is separated from whole milk.

value.value: An air filter is a device that removes some substance from air.

definition.value: This is a general definition derived from the definitions for particulate, chemical, and other air filters. Subclasses should be created if needed.

value.value: Limestone which is deposited from the water of mineral springs or streams saturated with calcium carbonate.
A building within which logs are cut into lumber products.
A large flat plain in karst territory with areas usually 5 to 400 sqaure kilometres.
